29/03/2004
LEIPZIG, Germany -- Bosnian writer Dzevad Karahasan was awarded the prestigious Leipzig Book Fair Prize for European Understanding on Sunday (28 March). The award and its accompanying 10,000-euro prize have been given every year since 1994 to writers who promote understanding among European nations. Karahasan's works focus on the aftermath of the 1992-1995 conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina. (AFP - 28/03/04)
